I personally am not in favor of this. It sounds good on paper, but hypothetically if i post a prop on like sunday, and vote would start on tuesday, now we make that queue wait 6 full days before the vote can start so it can start on monday? I think this would kill a lot of time. We also cannot force Nouns DAO votes to end on the same day, so voters will still need to be engaged frequently anyways because they won't change their cadience.

I think you're using one specific example to bring down the whole idea itself. In your example, if the prop is posted on Sunday, and the vote begins on mondays, then voting begins the next day. But lets use the example that a prop is put on chain on tuesday, this would mean that it will have to wait 6 days. What you are not accounting for is the behaviour change that a mechanism like this would introduce. Meaning, if people know props go live Mondays, then that extra time will likely be taken to refine and put the prop on chain on the weekend. Conversely, this will actually speed up some props, given that they wont need to wait 2 full days to go live, if they submit before a deadline on Sunday.

This is great! I would be happy to lead some usability testing on this too - so we can get some actionable data on how we can improve the product.

I do this with small product teams full of engineers at work. We call it "mob usability testing".  Basically, you have a dev team of ~3-5ish ppl hop on a zoom call with one user to do the "usability test" on. One person (usually PM or UXer) drives the questions/walkthrough while everyone else mute's mic's and turns off cameras. While walking through the product, the rest of the team writes out notes/observations on stickies on some sort of board (we use Miro). After the a couple of interviews, we synthesize feedback to expose pain area's, generate solutions, and do a group prioritization exercise.
If anyone is interested in this, just lmk. I'm in the discord - usually reading the LilNounsDAO channels.

Thank you wiz for providing much needed feedback on this prop. Even though you voted against this I still appreciate the valid criticism as I can use your feedback to try and tighten the prop with the greatest chance of passing.  As I continue to dwell on the idea, I am leaning towards splitting this into two phases:  phase 1: Pilot program -A significant less amount of ETH simply to create all the Nounish assets, add them to the game and make them publicly available for everyone, CC0 style. This makes the deliverables more easily digestible without complications from the gaming aspect of it.  phase 2: Scaling & tentative future gameplay developments -A separate prop in which we evaluate the community's reception from the added assets to see if it's worth funding it for future developments which I speak about in the "Future" section of the initial prop (multiplayer, NFT display integration, new gameplay mechanics, etc)  Your thoughts?

appreciate the feedback, I think the take on starting with smaller niche newsletters is an interesting take. I can see larger marketing initiative where we spread the message of Lil Nouns by sponsoring multiple smaller audience newsletters and podcasts. It's a great way to create some organic growth for the dao. With that said, numbers don't lie, we could exclude bankless with this proposal, still have the editorial interview where we are interviewed on the Green pill and drastically decrease overall costs. But 1.8 million DLs per month has a ton of potential value   The thing that's nice about this is it is a combined marketing outreach. We're getting the editorial interview which provides a deep dive into lil nouns dao while also shining a spotlight on the engaged community members. It gives dedicated members who are participating a platform to improve their social capital at the same time that we are promoting the community and pipeline of lilnounsdao.   The goal is to onboard new members into the community. Bankless is a trusted source of information in the the web3 world. New users often have a difficult time understanding which contracts or nft communities are legit and which are malicious. This marketing outreach effort helps to solidify our reputation by entering into the conversation with the bankless community as well as the gitcoin community which focuses on public goods and has a very large community of builders/devs. It will aso serve to open the door for dao-dao community relations.   My goal with the advertisement is to open with the activation of "robonoun" and then transition to shots where robonoun begins assembling the lil nouns logo with the help of other lil nouns then they present it to Nouns.
